  margin-bottom : 20%;

  padding:10px;
}

Interview Question
Q.Margin padding rule?

1 value : all sides

2 vlaue :top-bottom | right-left

3 value : top | right -left | bottom

4 value : top | right | bottom | left

margin is used to outside item to adjust
Padding for internal item to adjust

-Achor tag
Nothing but just clickable text
<a herf="hhtps://thekiranacademy.com">Vist to TKA </a> -- it open n same tag
To oepn in next tab
<a herf="htps://thekiranacademy.com" target= "blank">Vist to TKA </a>
<a herf="day02.html" target= "blank">Vist to TKA </a>  -- it can open the file  also after click

<br> -- for next line

It can use as like button


*****************************29th MAY
BootStrap,OL,UL,select, iframe, image tag

- Order List
    <ol>                          --> order list show sin number by default
        <li>Mango</li>            
        <li>Banana</li>
        <li>Grapse</li>
        <li>Kivi</li>
    </ol>


 <ol type ="A" >                          --> order list show in alphabatical order by (it can be shows as small alphabetical order, roman(i) )
        <li>Mango</li>            
        <li>Banana</li>
        <li>Grapse</li>
        <li>Kivi</li>
    </ol>

-Unorder List

 <ul>                          --> unorder list shows in bullet point by defualt 
        <li>Mango</li>            
        <li>Banana</li>
        <li>Grapse</li>
        <li>Kivi</li>
    </ul>

    to change the particular css then 

  ul li{
color : red
  }

if having id for list then

 <ul id = "fruit">                          --> unorder list shows in square point  
        <li>Mango</li>            
        <li>Banana</li>
        <li>Grapse</li>
        <li>Kivi</li>
    </ul>

#fruit li{

color :red;
list-style : sqaure;
}

- Select tag

select tag is a drop down menu. It is parent tag

<select>
  <option> MI</option>
<option selected> CSK</option>   --> selected attribute shows as CSK as first selected option 
<option> GT</option>
<option> KKR</option>

</select>

- TO select multiple option 

<select mutiple>
  <option> MI</option>
<option selected> CSK</option>    
<option> GT</option>
<option> KKR</option>

</select>

so we can select mutiple option 


- If want to see 3 option

<select mutiple size="3">
  <option> MI</option>
<option selected> CSK</option>    
<option> GT</option>
<option> KKR</option>

</select>

If want to disabled to option but not delete the option


<select mutiple size="3">
  <option> MI</option>
<option selected> CSK</option>    
<option> GT</option>
<option disabled> KKR</option>

</select>

To generate different option

<select>
<optgroup label ="Major citie>
<option >Pune</option>
<option >Delhi</option>
<option >Banglore</option>
<option >Hyderabad</option>
</optgroup>
                                                --> this is shown as first shows major cities under that shows option and All cities under shows option
<optiongroup label ="All cities">
<option>Amravati</option>
<option>Bhed</option>
<option>Chandrapur</option>
<option>Darypur</option>
</optgroup>

</select>

- Image tag  

Image tag is used for to show the image 

<img src= "samsung s4ultra.png" alt="samsung image" >  --> alt is use for alternate message (if image crash the show the message samsunng image)

To manage the size of image
 img{
height: 450px;
width:650px;
margin-left :40%;
box-shadow: 10px 50px 5px 20px black;  -> 1st value : left to right
                                          2nd value  : up to down
                                          3rd value : bacjground blur
                                          4th value : background dark
 }

- Bootstrap
To apply the bootstrap we have to  attach the CDN link in link tag for html

- iframe

to show the other frame in the project 
<iframe src= "http://thekiranacademy.com/" frameborder="0"></iframe> --> so in the website able to seee the kiranacademy website



